LC6Cmax3 Kate - cross
1 A. Could have been.
2 Q. And at that time, you had a very large Great Dane; correct?
3 A. At which time?
4 Q. At the time you made that statement when you said the other 10 percent was thinking about your dog?
5 A. I don't remember which dog it was at that time, but it's possible.
6 Q. In around 2004, you did have a Great Dane, didn't you?
7 A. I don't remember the date, but I did have a Great Dane, that I did used to have a Great Dane.
8 Q. But there was a period in time in which you became very well known as a model; correct?
9 A. I was not very well known.
10 Q. Well, you were on billboards, weren't you?
11 A. I was on a billboard once.
12 Q. And you were a model for a U.K. version of Victoria's Secret, weren't you?
13 A. No.
14 Q. You never were a model for an organization that sold lingerie?
15 A. I was a model for a lingerie company that failed almost as soon as it began.
16 Q. But it was a lingerie company?
17 A. Yes.
18 Q. And you also were a model for clothing, weren't you?
19 A. Yes.
20 SOUTHERN DISTRICT REPORTERS, P.C. (212) 805-0300
